$ with projected separation $a_{1,\\perp}=1.4\\,$au.\nHowever, there is a relatively bright $I=18.6$ (and also relatively blue) star\nprojected within $<50\\,$mas of the lens, and if future high-resolution images\nshow that this is coincident with the lens, then it is possible that it is the\nlens, in which case, the lens would be both more massive and more distant than\nthe best-estimated values above.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 May 2019 03:06:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-07"}
